    <h3>Training Quality</h3>
    <p>The TOFFEE method training — a Facebook-centric prospecting and sales system — is the primary advanced training exclusive to Community Builders. Multiple sources describe it as a multi-hour course covering audience warm-up and warm-down routines, posting frameworks, direct messaging scripts, and Zoom sales call techniques. Weekly "guru huddles" (reportedly five per week from different topic-specialist trainers) and topic-specific coaching sessions on solo ads, YouTube ads, and email marketing are also cited as included benefits. Independent reviewers consistently note that most training is heavily skewed toward Facebook organic methods and OLSP-centric funnels rather than SEO, content marketing, or platform-independent list building.</p>

    <h3>Traffic Tools</h3>
    <p>Two traffic-related features are cited for Community Builders. First, the traffic rotator: a pool of solo-ad traffic purchased by OLSP leadership and distributed across participating members. Independent reviewers note that with tens of thousands of OLSP affiliates sharing the same rotator, internal traffic may be diluted and should not be treated as a primary strategy. Second, Viral Hub credits: approximately 1,000 credits per month to fund incentivized engagement campaigns (pay-per-comment and interaction campaigns) within the OLSP community. These are useful for community stimulation but are not the same as qualified buyer traffic from an external source.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="ux">
    <h2>User Experience</h2>

    <h3>Setup Process</h3>
    <p>Community Builders is purchased as an upgrade to an existing OLSP account — there is no standalone sign-up path. Members go through an upgrade funnel inside OLSP or via an affiliate's sales page, which adds the Community Builders tier to their existing account. Once active, the Mega Builder software access and enhanced commission rates reportedly take effect immediately. Members who bundle their purchase through an individual affiliate's link may also receive the affiliate's personal bonus stack (extra coaching, tool credits, content), which varies by promoter and is not part of the core product.</p>

    <h3>Daily Usage</h3>
    <p>Based on vendor training descriptions and independent reviewer accounts, active Community Builders usage centers on: publishing regular Facebook content using the TOFFEE method framework; sending direct messages to warm prospects and following scripted DM sequences; attending or replaying live guru huddles and coaching calls; inviting prospects into your private OLSP community; and monitoring your OLSP dashboard for lead tracking and commission activity. Multiple sources suggest 30 or more minutes per day as a minimum commitment for the tier to justify its recurring cost.</p>

    <h3>Learning Curve</h3>
    <p>Reviewers describe a steeper learning curve at Community Builders compared to the Megalink level, primarily because the TOFFEE method requires consistent social content habits and active direct outreach skills developed over time. The Mega Builder software — being based on GoHighLevel — is documented externally and described as reasonably capable, but configuring funnels, email sequences, and CRM pipelines to work effectively with OLSP's system requires setup time and some technical comfort.</p>

    <h3>Interface &amp; Community</h3>
    <p>We could not independently assess the dashboard interface. Independent reviewers describe the OLSP member area as reasonably organized, but most of these sources carry their own referral links and cannot be considered neutral assessments. The OLSP Facebook community reportedly has 200,000 or more members and is described as active across multiple sources. Some Reddit commenters allege that sceptical or critical posts are blocked in the group — a claim that could not be independently confirmed.</p>
  </section>

