  <section id="history">
    <h2>History &amp; Updates</h2>
    <p>Wayne Crowe is the founder and CEO of OLSP System/Academy, described publicly as a British affiliate marketer from Norwich. Vendor materials and the OLSP support portal credit him with over $15 million in affiliate commissions — a self-reported figure that appears consistently across official and affiliate sources but could not be independently verified. He had previously run a related program called Traffic Domination before building OLSP. The OLSP System was launched publicly around 2019–2020 and has been extended and relaunched multiple times.</p>

    <p>Marketing pages found in 2026 reference an "OLSP System Relaunch" and updated tier structures. Whether this represents a substantive platform overhaul or primarily a new promotional campaign layered on top of the existing system could not be confirmed from publicly available information alone. The Community Builders tier, as described in current affiliate and vendor materials, appears to be a longstanding component of the OLSP upgrade ladder rather than a newly introduced feature.</p>

    <Callout type="info">
      <strong>Due-diligence note:</strong> When evaluating any relaunch claim, verify whether the core product mechanics, pricing, and terms have meaningfully changed — or whether a "relaunch" primarily describes new marketing for an existing product. OLSP's support portal and official domains are the most reliable starting point for current information.
    </Callout>
  </section>

  <section id="recommend">
    <h2>Who Should Join OLSP Community Builders?</h2>

    <h3>Best For</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Existing OLSP members who have completed Megalink training and are already promoting on a regular basis.</li>
      <li>Affiliates who can commit at least 30 minutes per day to Facebook content creation, direct messaging, and live event participation.</li>
      <li>People who want an integrated marketing software stack (funnel builder, CRM, email automations) tightly configured for OLSP's product offers, without separately subscribing to each tool.</li>
      <li>Members interested in building a recruited team of affiliates and earning second-tier commissions from their team's activity — not just their own promotions.</li>
      <li>People who value structured live coaching and community accountability as part of their learning and motivation system.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Skip If</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>You're brand new to OLSP and haven't validated results through the Megalink and Live Profit Builders levels. Most independent reviewers, including some who promote Community Builders, recommend against jumping to this tier without first completing the base training.</li>
      <li>Your available time is limited or unpredictable. Attending live huddles and maintaining a daily Facebook content schedule are described as central to getting value from this tier.</li>
      <li>You already have independent funnels, a CRM, and an email list, and primarily want to promote offers outside the OLSP ecosystem — in that case the OLSP-specific tools may deliver less incremental value.</li>
      <li>You prefer SEO, blogging, or YouTube as primary traffic channels. The TOFFEE method and most Community Builders training is explicitly built around Facebook organic methods.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Alternatives Worth Comparing</h3>
    <p>Before committing to Community Builders' recurring cost, consider: remaining at the Live Profit Builders tier ($49/month) while you build consistent results and active traffic, then upgrading when the 200% commissions and second-tier earnings clearly justify the additional cost; subscribing directly to GoHighLevel as a standalone tool if you need the software features without the OLSP-specific training and commission layer; or exploring general affiliate networks that let you promote independent products without a single-vendor upgrade funnel. It is also worth comparing Team Builders' lifetime pricing (~$997) against paying Community Builders' monthly fee over many months, depending on your long-term commitment to the OLSP ecosystem.</p>
  </section>

